{"questionId":"9508","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the integral&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\int\\limits_1^t {\\frac{{ - 1}}{{x + {x^2}}}{\\text{ }}} dx\">\n  <munderover>\n    <mo>∫</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mi>t</mi>\n  </munderover>\n  <mrow>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mo>−</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mi>x</mi>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>x</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtext>&nbsp;</mtext>\n    </mrow>\n  </mrow>\n  <mi>d</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> for&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t > 1\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>&gt;</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Very briefly, explain why the value of this integral must be negative.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>The numerator is negative but the denominator is positive. Thus the integrand is negative and so the value of the integral will be negative.&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9508","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Very briefly, explain why the value of this integral must be negative.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.11—Partial fractions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}